.IP "\fBDtNmarginHeight\fP"
\fIDtNmarginHeight\fP specifies the number of pixels added between the top and
bottom of the text widget and the start of the shadow.
.IP "\fBDtNmarginWidth\fP"
\fIDtNmarginWidth\fP specifies the number of pixels added between the right and
left sides of the text widget and the start of the shadow.
.IP "\fBDtNselectedItem\fP"
This resource is passed through to the XmList to set the
\fIXmNselectedItemCount\fP and \fIXmNselectedItems\fP as the single item
in the XmNitems that matches this specified XmString in the List.
Setting both \fIDtNselectedItem\fP and \fIDtNselectedPosition\fP in the
same ArgList has undefined behavior.
.IP "\fBDtNselectedPosition\fP"
This resource is passed through to the XmList to set the
\fIXmNselectedItemCount\fP and \fIXmNselectedItems\fP as the single item
at this specified position in the List.
Setting both \fIDtNselectedItem\fP and \fIDtNselectedPosition\fP in the
same ArgList has undefined behavior.
.IP "\fBDtNselectionCallback\fP"
This callback list is issued when an item is selected from the DtComboBox
widget's List.
The call_data structure contains a DtComboBoxCallbackStruct with the
reason DtCR_SELECT. 
This structure is defined below.
.IP "\fBDtNcomboBoxType\fP"
This resource determines the style of the DtComboBox.
There are two choices:
.wH
.rS
.TP
\(bu
\fIDtDROP_DOWN_COMBO_BOX\fP
.TP
\(bu
\fIDtDROP_DOWN_LIST\fP
.wH
.rE
.nL
.IP
The DtDROP_DOWN_COMBO_BOX style type provides an editable text area, and the 
DtDROP_DOWN_LIST provides a static text area.
.sp .5
