.SS "Callback Information"
A pointer to the following structure is passed to each DtComboBox callback:
.sp .5
.nf
.ta .25i 1.1i
\fBtypedef struct \fP{
	\fBint\fP 	\fIreason\fP;
	\fBXEvent\fP	\fI* event\fP;
	\fBXmString\fP	\fIitem_or_text\fP;
	\fBint\fP	\fIitem_position\fP;
} \fBDtComboBoxCallbackStruct\fP;
.fi
.sp .5
.IP "\fIreason\fP"
There is only one possible reason for this callback to be issued, DtCR_SELECT.
.IP "\fIevent\fP"
A pointer to the event that caused this callback to be invoked. It can 
be NULL.
.IP "\fIitem_or_text\fP"
The contents of the Text widget at the time the event caused the 
callback to be invoked.
This data is only valid within the scope of the call_data structure,
so it must be copied when it is used outside of this scope.
.IP "\fIitem_position\fP"
The new value of the \fIDtNposition\fP resource in the DtComboBox's List.
If this is 0, it means the user entered a value in the XmTextField widget.
